# Example HTTP host routing for Boxion edge proxy
#
# Map $host to an upstream. You can route the dashboard/API to the api container
# and any other public sites to their IPv6 Boxion addresses (handled by ndppd/WireGuard).
# The default (in nginx.conf) is caddy:8080 if no match is found.
#
# Syntax: <hostname> <upstream>;
#
# Route dashboard to API container (HTTP)
# Replace with your domain used to access the dashboard/API
#
# tunnel.milkywayhub.org   api:8080;
#
# Example: route a public site to its Boxion-assigned IPv6 on port 80
# site1.example.org        [2001:db8:1234:5678::120]:80;
